sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Cli as Client
    participant OA as Origin A · handles the append
    participant R as Redis · slot {__ds:h}
    participant OB as Origin B · owns slot h
    participant Recv as Receiver
    Cli->>OA: POST events/abc + body
    OA->>R: append.lua — durable write to events/abc
    OA-->>Cli: 204 · the byte is committed
    Note over OA,R: OnStreamAppend: S parallel SMEMBERS over occupied slots → sub-1 lives in slot h
    OA->>R: arm_wake.lua on {__ds:h} — generation++ · ZADD {__ds:h}:due now
    OA->>Recv: POST signed wake — fast path, the appending origin delivers
    Recv-->>OA: 200 {done:true}
    OA->>R: ack.lua on {__ds:h} — cursor → tail · ZREM {__ds:h}:due
    Note over OB: Origin B owns slot h — its due-worker finds the due-set empty, nothing owed, no redundant delivery
